  "topic_id": "T04.07",
  "topic_name": "Rectilinear Figures",
  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "Rectilinear figures are polygons with straight sides. Key properties include: (1) The sum of interior angles of an n-sided polygon is (n-2) × 180°. (2) Parallelograms have opposite sides equal and parallel, opposite angles equal, and diagonals bisecting each other. (3) Special parallelograms include rectangles (all angles 90°), rhombuses (all sides equal), and squares (all sides equal and all angles 90°). (4) Trapeziums have one pair of parallel sides, and isosceles trapeziums have non-parallel sides equal. (5) Properties can be proved using triangle congruence criteria (SSS, SAS, ASA, RHS).",
    "rules": [
      "Interior angle sum of n-sided polygon = (n-2) × 180°",
      "Each interior angle of regular n-sided polygon = (n-2) × 180° / n",
      "In parallelograms: opposite sides are equal and parallel",
      "In parallelograms: opposite angles are equal",
      "In parallelograms: diagonals bisect each other",
      "In rectangles: all angles are 90° and diagonals are equal",
      "In rhombus: all sides are equal and diagonals are perpendicular",
      "In square: all sides equal, all angles 90°, diagonals equal and perpendicular",
      "In trapezium: one pair of opposite sides is parallel",
      "In isosceles trapezium: non-parallel sides are equal and base angles are equal"
    ]
  },
